    e.
        The microprocessor analyses the data which has been taken in by the sensor at the barrier, and then sends signals to control whether or not the barrier is raised. It may validate the ticket number e.g. by computing a check digit or checksum to ensure there has been no mis-read by the scanner or to defeat trivial attempts at falsification. It will then likely compare the ticket number with a list of valid ticket numbers which the payment-machine has issued.
