    b?
        When a key is pressed on a keyboard, a signal is sent from the keyboard to the processor. This causes the processor to stop whatever it is executing and begin running operating system code, which uses drivers to handle the keypress. After the keypress is handled, the previous state of the previous process is restored, and execution continues.
